Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and the sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until well blended. Gently stir in 1-1/2 cups of the whipped topping. Spread onto bottom of crust. Pour 2 cups milk into another large bowl. Add dry pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir in the remaining whipped topping. Spread over cream cheese layer in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Store leftovers in refrigerator.